<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 25 at 8:41PM EDT  by NWS State College</headline>
<description>...A STRONG THUNDERSTORM WILL IMPACT SOUTHWESTERN BEDFORD COUNTY
THROUGH 915 PM EDT...
At 840 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Bedford, moving northeast at 10 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Clearville and Rainsburg.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
